# Generated Slide PDF Policy

- HTML, CSS, JavaScript, data, and images are source. `L*.pdf` files are generated.
- During local QA, render PDFs to `/tmp`; do not overwrite or stage tracked PDFs.
- Commit and push source changes only. `.github/workflows/slides-pdf.yml` regenerates and commits PDFs.
- Before an ordinary source commit, verify `git diff --cached --name-only` contains no slide PDFs. A merge commit may carry PDFs already generated by the bot.
- Before starting new slide work, fetch/rebase the latest `origin/master` so the bot PDF commit is present locally.
- If PDFs conflict, resolve the source files first. Do not merge binary PDF contents; accept either generated side to finish the merge, then let CI overwrite it from the merged source.
- Only commit PDFs manually when the user explicitly requests bypassing the PDF workflow.
